[ 0, 6, 7, 8, 9, 12 ]
Thus, \(S = \{0, 6, 7, 8, 9, 12, \rightarrow \} = T\) and the result holds. The function IsAperyListOfNumericalSemigroup returns true or false depending on whether a list of integers may represent the ApÃ©ry set of a numerical semigroup.
gap&gt; IsAperyListOfNumericalSemigroup([ 0, 7, 8, 9, 16, 17 ]);
true

