Nowadays, there are no functions in package NumericalSgps related to reduction of proper ideals. However, given a numerical semigroup \(S\) and two proper ideals \(H,E\) of \(S\), the following function returns true if \(H\) is a reduction of \(E\) and false otherwise.
gap&gt; IsReduction := function(S,J,I)
&gt;       if not IsNumericalSemigroup(S) then
&gt;               Error("First argument must be a Numerical Semigroup");
&gt;       fi;
&gt;       if not IsIdealOfNumericalSemigroup(J) then
&gt;               Error("Second argument must be a relative ideal")
&gt;       fi;
&gt;       if not IsIdealOfNumericalSemigroup(I) then
&gt;               Error("Third argument must be a relative ideal")
&gt;       fi;
&gt;       if not (IsSubset(0+S,J) and IsSubset(0+S,I)) then
&gt;               return false;
&gt;       elif not (IsIntegral(J) and IsIntegral(I)) then
&gt;               return false;
&gt;       fi;
&gt;       if IsSubset(J, Minimum(I) + S) and IsSubset(I,J) then
&gt;               return true;
&gt;       fi;
&gt;       return false;
&gt; end;
\(\diamond\) Let \(S = \langle 13, 15, 22, 27 \rangle\), \(I = \{26, 28, 40, 41\} + S\) and \(J = \{26, 41\} + S\), in GAP:
