&lt;Ideal of numerical semigroup&gt;
gap&gt; J := [26, 41] + S;
&lt;Ideal of numerical semigroup&gt;
Since \(I,J \subseteq S\) are proper ideals and \(m(I) + S \subseteq J \subseteq I\), then \(J\) is a reduction of \(I\).
